{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.34",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 34,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 34",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 34 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:1",
      "text": "Furthermore Elihu answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:2",
      "text": "Hear my words, O ye wise men; and give ear unto me, ye that have knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:3",
      "text": "For the ear trieth words, as the mouth tasteth meat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:4",
      "text": "Let us choose to us judgment: let us know among ourselves what is good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:5",
      "text": "For Job hath said, I am righteous: and God hath taken away my judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:6",
      "text": "Should I lie against my right? my wound is incurable without transgression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:7",
      "text": "What man is like Job, who drinketh up scorning like water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:8",
      "text": "Which goeth in company with the workers of iniquity, and walketh with wicked men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:9",
      "text": "For he hath said, It profiteth a man nothing that he should delight himself with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:10",
      "text": "Therefore hearken unto me, ye men of understanding: far be it from God, that he should do wickedness; and from the Almighty, that he should commit iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:11",
      "text": "For the work of a man shall he render unto him, and cause every man to find according to his ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:12",
      "text": "Yea, surely God will not do wickedly, neither will the Almighty pervert judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:13",
      "text": "Who hath given him a charge over the earth? or who hath disposed the whole world?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:14",
      "text": "If he set his heart upon man, if he gather unto himself his spirit and his breath;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:15",
      "text": "All flesh shall perish together, and man shall turn again unto dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:16",
      "text": "If now thou hast understanding, hear this: hearken to the voice of my words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:17",
      "text": "Shall even he that hateth right govern? and wilt thou condemn him that is most just?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:18",
      "text": "Is it fit to say to a king, Thou art wicked? and to princes, Ye are ungodly?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:19",
      "text": "How much less to him that accepteth not the persons of princes, nor regardeth the rich more than the poor? for they all are the work of his hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:20",
      "text": "In a moment shall they die, and the people shall be troubled at midnight, and pass away: and the mighty shall be taken away without hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:21",
      "text": "For his eyes are upon the ways of man, and he seeth all his goings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:22",
      "text": "There is no darkness, nor shadow of death, where the workers of iniquity may hide themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:23",
      "text": "For he will not lay upon man more than right; that he should enter into judgment with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:24",
      "text": "He shall break in pieces mighty men without number, and set others in their stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:25",
      "text": "Therefore he knoweth their works, and he overturneth them in the night, so that they are destroyed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:26",
      "text": "He striketh them as wicked men in the open sight of others;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:27",
      "text": "Because they turned back from him, and would not consider any of his ways:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:28",
      "text": "So that they cause the cry of the poor to come unto him, and he heareth the cry of the afflicted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:29",
      "text": "When he giveth quietness, who then can make trouble? and when he hideth his face, who then can behold him? whether it be done against a nation, or against a man only:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:30",
      "text": "That the hypocrite reign not, lest the people be ensnared.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:31",
      "text": "Surely it is meet to be said unto God, I have borne chastisement, I will not offend any more:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:32",
      "text": "That which I see not teach thou me: if I have done iniquity, I will do no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:33",
      "text": "Should it be according to thy mind? he will recompense it, whether thou refuse, or whether thou choose; and not I: therefore speak what thou knowest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:34",
      "text": "Let men of understanding tell me, and let a wise man hearken unto me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:35",
      "text": "Job hath spoken without knowledge, and his words were without wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:36",
      "text": "My desire is that Job may be tried unto the end because of his answers for wicked men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.34.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:37",
      "text": "For he addeth rebellion unto his sin, he clappeth his hands among us, and multiplieth his words against God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
